cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "MeritKV: Novel Per-Request Utility Decisions for Waste-Aware KV Cache Reuse"
message: "If you use this repository, please cite the project."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Khemani
    given-names: Kushal
  - family-names: Leri
    given-names: Evan
  - family-names: Mittal
    given-names: Sparsh
version: 0.3.0
license: "MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Kushalk0677/shadowkv"
abstract: >
  MeritKV is a per-request policy controller for KV cache reuse in LLM
  serving. Instead of treating reuse as a yes/no prefix-cache decision, it
  scores whether reuse helps the current request. The controller can admit
  reuse, bypass low-utility candidates, account for wasted speculative work,
  and record semantic reuse opportunities without blindly executing unsafe
  approximate KV substitution.
